gomodel:SYNGO_4677  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1: KIF5C shRNA reduced spine density and spontaneous (mini) frequency and amplitude in mouse primary neuronal culture\nFig. 2: over expression of full length WT KIF5C increases mini amplitude (not frequency), and dendrite arborisation and spine density\nFig 4: WT KIF5C over expression increases translation in synaptosomes (puromycin labeling). Experimental description: \"For the primary cell culture preparation, pregnant CD1 mice (Charles River Laboratories) were used\"" ;
